11:
Didn't know the guy had it in him to
oversleep. I'll go get him.
20:
Guys, we've got a situation! Nimbus
has been KIDNAPPED! I... I THINK?!
24: What are you going on about?
27:
I know it sounds crazy, but I found
this letter in his room... Just look at it!
31:
"The tiger lost his gamble, and now
he's mine. Bring me Naska Etrange if
you want to see him again."
40:
Sh-should we alert the authorities?
But then Nimbus might—
44:
Take a deep breath. Judging by
what's written, Nimbus should be
safe, because the real target is...
48:
Hmm... Never expected them to pull
this.
55:
Not the exact identity of this
particular perpetrator, but I've got a
good guess as to the motive of
whoever's pulling the strings.
58: I'll play their game. I'm all in!
61:
Been a while, Naska. To think that
you were alive this whole time.
63:
So it's you and yours that are behind
this. I'm starting to see the picture
here.
69:
We used to work together back in
the day. Every time we meet up now,
he keeps pestering me to go back.
71:
...I take it from your tone that you'll
be rejecting me today too.
74:
Sorry, but I'm in the middle of the
biggest gamble of my life. I don't
have time to revisit old haunts.
76: I'll keep this simple for you.
78:
You and I will compete against one
another.
79:
If you win, the tiger is yours. But if I
win... both you and him are coming
with me.
87:
You're actually just gonna gamble
away both your lives without
hesitating?!
98:
Same rules we used to run with, I'm
assuming? Seven rounds, loser
decides the game for new rounds.
105: To see what Lady Luck has in store!
110:
How could you of all people lose
three rounds in a row? Have you
grown rusty in my absence?
114:
This is not looking good! If we don't
do something, our friends are gonna
get dragged away!
118:
Lower your voice! We're not allowed
to interfere with their match, but
perhaps we can free Nimbus from
his bindings...
123:
Everything will be okay. Naska is
smiling.
132:
Sorry, sorry, you're probably right
that I'm a little rusty.
135:
But isn't it so much more exciting
when the stakes are high?
138:
Cut the chatter and tell me what the
next game is! I'll finish this once and
for all!
140: You want to do a coin toss?!
146: So what will it be—heads or tails?
149:
Tch... Whatever, victory will still be
mine! Tails!
158:
Damn it... One loss means nothing!
This match isn't over yet!
161:
Sure isn't! I'd be disappointed if we
were done already!
167:
I feel like I lost ten years off my life...
You good, Nimbus?
170:
Sure took your time. It was so boring
trying to sit still.
175:
Hold on... Don't tell me you weren't
actually...
178:
...I just want to know one thing—what
is this "biggest gamble of your life"
that you are so intent on seeing
through?
181:
It's these folks here with me. The
lives of everyone in the world
depend on them... but I'm confident I
placed my bets on the right crowd.
184:
Is that right... I suppose you were
always one to go for the craziest
gambles.
